RACE.FOOTNOTES: HEJAZI broke a step slow then went up to take control from inside, set the pace under pressure from SULLY, shook free into the stretch and held safely under hand urging. WORCESTER broke well and settled into a stalking position off the rail, went two wide into the turn, moved out and took aim three wide into the lane, finished determinedly through the lane and closed the gap on the winner while proving second best. SULLY brushed the gate but still came away quickly, pressed HEJAZI from outside into and around the turn, lost touch with that rival into the stretch and flattened to third. I DON'T GET IT hit the gate to come away a bit slow, had to steady early, steered to the inside and moved into range, traveled a bit off the rail into the lane and lacked a late bid. TIZ TOK settled off the pace, rounded the bend two wide and could not rally. SPEED OF THE NILE was off slow and bobbled at the start, split foes through a tight spot early, chased three deep into the turn, continued three wide into the lane and weakened. THE LAST ONE PERK threw his head at the start and bobbled a bit to come away slow, lagged behind up the backstretch off the rail, angled to the inside around the turn and was not a factor.

SECRET SQUARE led two wide into the first turn then lost command around the bend, chased briefly then went up to press the pace from outside on the backstretch, stayed alongside then failed to keep up with a quarter mile left to run and weakened in the lane. RED FLAG tracked outside rivals three to four wide around the clubhouse turn, was asked four then three deep on the far turn but flattened out in the stretch. MIDNIGHT MAMMOTH sent from the gate, dueled with HERO STATUS before taking control around the clubhouse turn, set a pressured pace then raced on even terms at the half-mile pole, could not keep up pat the seven-sixteenths pole, lost ground and came four wide into the stretch and tired. BOLD ENDEAVOR chased two to three wide early between rivals, coaxed along up the backstretch, got blocked on the far turn and angled to the inside, then weakened in the stretch run.

LOOKS RARE away quickly from inside then drifted out prior to the first turn, dueled three wide into the bend, angled to the rail and ceded control to LOW EXPECTATIONS, switched to the outside of that rival, applied pressure at the half-mile pole, lost tough briefly then re-engaged the leader at the quarter pole, fought through the lane from outside but could not get by. DEEP RIVER got shuffled back between rivals early, chased off the rail and steadied when LOOKS RARE angled out on the first turn, tracked four wide into the second bend, angled down to the two path and lacked a rally. GLENDALE had his path taken and clipped heels in the beginning, trailed on the inside, came two wide into the stretch and failed to menace. DONTTESTYOURLUCK got shuffled between rivals early, chased five then four wide on the first turn, remained wide into the second bend, moved down to the two path, came three wide into the stretch and had little left for the drive. REIGN OVER ME bumped and checked between foes early, chased six then five wide early on, entered the far turn six wide, moved down to the three path, came four wide into the drive and failed to menace.

SONIC BREES chased three deep into the turn, asked three wide into the lane and edged SAWASDEE for the place honors. SAWASDEE sprinted clear and crossed over, led along the rail into the turn, challenged from outside at the five-sixteenths pole, lost command at the quarter pole, fought on to the eighth pole then could not go on with the winner and got edged for the place. RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRAEGAR stalked the leaders from outside early, bid three deep around the bend, dueled outside HOPKINS in the stretch, put in nose in front entering the final sixteenth and dug in late to prevail. HOPKINS pressed the pace from inside then moved up to duel leaving the backstretch, took over and vied with rivals past the five-sixteenths pole, held a short lead over TRAEGAR entering the final furlong, lost the lead outside the sixteenth pole but fought back gamely to the wire. MCLAREN VALE broke a step slow, was coaxed to a forward position early, raced in the two path nearing the turn then angled to the inside, saved ground to the stretch while being asked and failed to offer the needed response. I GOT NO MUNNY stalked from inside early then shifted to the two path nearing the turn, steered out and came four wide into the lane and lacked a rally. RACE.RACE_TEXT: La Canada S. - Grade3 SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 7 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 96. Stakes Purse 200000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES, FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Thursday, January 5, 2023, closed with 13 or by Supplementary nomination of $4,000 due at time of entry. $1,500 to enter and an additional $1,500 to start with $200,000 guaranteed of which $120,000 to the winner, $40,000 to second, $24,000 to third, $12,000 to fourth, and $4,000 to fifth. 124 lbs. Non-Winners of a Graded Stakes at One Mile or Over allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of Sweepstakes at One Mile or Ov er allowed 4 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KIRSTENBOSCH coaxed early chasing from along the rail, ridden along into the far turn, asked around right handed around the bend, took aim two to three wide into the stretch, moved out further in the lane, drew alongside GANADORA in the final sixteenth, took a bump from that rival and got up at the wire. GANADORA was antsy in the gate, broke out and bumped rival, sped to the front in the two path then cleared inner rival and moved inside, took pressure from outside up the backstretch, dueled around the far turn and lost command at the quarter pole, fought back from inside and regained the lead in upper stretch, shook free past the eighth pole, challenged by KIRSTENBOSCH with a sixteenth remaining, drifted out and bumped that rival and was nailed on the line. SMOOTHLIKEBUTTAH hopped slightly and got bumped by GANADORA at the start, tucked inside at the back early, passed a few rivals then gained ground through the far turn, tipped out into the stretch and edged ANGEL NADESHIKO for the show honors. ANGEL NADESHIKO was antsy in the gate, raced up close on the inside then ceded control to GANADORA, switched to the outside and went up to press the pace, dueled on the far turn and took over at the quarter pole, relinquished the lead in upper stretch, flattened in the late stages and lost the show. UNDER THE STARS chased three wide early, asked nearing the seven-sixteenths pole, weakened on the far turn, eased through the stretch and walked off. NATURAL COLOUR (GB) was antsy in the gate, stalked outside a rival early, dropped back to last leaving the backstretch, tired on the far turn, eased in the lane and walked off.
